      "memo": "Enterprise RAG switching costs are low: the retrieval corpus transfers between model providers with minimal integration rework.",
      "detail": "The enterprise owns the document corpus independently of any model or platform provider. Switching language models requires prompt re-engineering but not data migration. Vector-database portability enables infrastructure provider switches. Low switching costs are a designed feature of the RAG architecture."
    },
    "Exit": {
      "value": "Clean",
      "memo": "Enterprise RAG exit is clean: inference-only processing means no enterprise data is entangled in model weights, enabling complete separation.",
      "detail": "Enterprise data passes through the model at inference time without modifying weights. Terminating the model-provider relationship leaves no residual capability in the provider's systems. The clean-exit property is RAG's primary governance advantage over training-based approaches. Architectural separation between data and model is what makes clean exit possible."
    },
